{"tid":1875870,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"英國帝國學院最新報告：初步估計，武漢肺炎死亡率係大約 1%","createTime":"2020-02-12T05:02:06.000Z","updateTime":"2020-02-13T12:58:00.000Z","uid":48083,"like":2,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":19,"replies":[{"pid":"1c839f51bec28c8ae99d97976df97a2e678be76f","tid":1875870,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-12T05:02:06.000Z","msg":"A key measure of severity of any outbreak is the case fatality ratio (CFR) - the proportion of people with a disease who will eventually die as a result of infection. Quantifying this can be challenging.⋯⋯⋯<br />\n<br />\n In Hubei province in China, only people with relatively severe symptoms are being prioritised for testing. Their central estimate of CFR for these cases is 18%, but with high uncertainty.⋯⋯<br />\n<br />\nOur best estimate is that the fatality ratio for all infections is roughly 1%, but there remains uncertainty and we will update our analyses as further data become available.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/195217/coronavirus-fatality-rate-estimated-imperial-scientists/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imperial.ac.uk%2Fnews%2F195217%2Fcoronavirus-fatality-rate-estimated-imperial-scientists%2F&d=k4A9UPuxEtmwSexvyTVA%2BZMONXnVHdpXbsFGehQCOpI%3D&h=617d851b\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/195217/coronavirus-fatality-rate-estimated-imperial-scientists/</a>"},{"pid":"a8a5d453988e2ef8707b193894be72b184e8985c","tid":1875870,"uid":57674,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-12T05:02:40.000Z","msg":"但支那已經唔止1%喇喎"},{"pid":"f1e92d51053f894e01bdf4b000fdc0b5f2265715","tid":1875870,"uid":155095,"like":7,"dislike":2,"score":5,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-12T05:03:14.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"color: red;\">英國研究</span> <img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9c56ab61a9663be5b4293a9e74ef0861182dc53f","tid":1875870,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":2,"scor